This is my first article published with bazinga. It will show you some features now:

[b]bold text[/b] is as easy to write as [u]underlined text[/u]. [i]italic text[/i] too, of course.

If you want to insert a code snipped, bazinga has a special feature for that:

LATEX_START
\mathcal B}(t\bar{t} \rightarrow W b Z c) = 
\frac{ N_\mathrm{candidates} - N_\mathrm{background} }
{{\mathcal A} \cdot \int {\mathcal L} dt \cdot \sigma_{t \bar{t}}}
LATEX_END

LATEX_START
<math>  
\begin{equation*}R = \frac{  
\displaystyle{\sum_{i=1}^n (x_i-\bar{x})(y_i-  
\bar{y})}}{\displaystyle{\left[  
\sum_{i=1}^n(x_i-\bar{x})^2  
\sum_{i=1}^n(y_i-\bar{y})^2\right]^{1/2}}}  
\end{equation*}  
</math>
LATEX_END

LATEX_START
<math>  
\setlength{\unitlength}{0.8cm}  
\begin{picture}(6,4)   
